2026-04-16 12:10:09 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Battery connection / source polarity', 'PSU output-to-control input cable pairing'] hypothesis_explanation='Root cause is a polarity/configuration error, not a failed component. The 12 V source is wired with reversed polarity with respect to the system’s defined ground (battery ‘+’ at –12 V). In addition, the PSU output leads are connected to the control module inputs in a way that assumes correct battery polarity, so with the battery reversed the control-module LED becomes forward‑biased (lights) while the PSU green LED is reverse‑biased (off) and the load-module diode blocks current to the lamp. Correcting the battery/source polarity (and if necessary swapping the PSU output cables at the control module so that the designated + and – lines correspond to actual +12 V and 0 V) will restore proper function: PSU green LED on, control red LED off, and main lamp operating when the switch is closed.'
